comments.text: In this particular case I feel like the overall evidence kinda goes against the likelihood of foul play. If they got kidnapped the first thing the kidnapper would do is strip them of their belongings/take control of their phones.... however in this case they showed a pattern of checking their phones consistently so it's pretty likely they had free will and were not being controlled by anyone. Probably just a sad case of 2 very ignorant girls who were used to their small home town hiking trails and didn't understand the scope of what they were entering, mindlessly taking pics and having a good time until a couple hours pass and they realize they have been careless, and have no idea how to get back... usually not an issue in city environments but in the jungle it's like a whole different world. As for the bodies, they are in the wild, when they died animals most likely ate them/scattered the remains around. Such a sad case of people who were never educated on how dangerous getting lost can truly be and were too dependent on their phones which turned out to be useless (they weren't used to or probably even thought dead zones were a thing)
